Basic commands:

run (or create) a  session
1. save temp data
2. save session
    a) to the api
    b) to the local file

Create a new scene
1. create a new file in the appropriate project/book folder, including yaml header
2. create a new record in the API, related to the appropriate project
3. (tentative) add a json representation to a novel.json or scenes.json file

Create a new project (=book)
1. Create a directory in the appropriate world/project, including standard structure:
BOOK
├── manuscript
│         ├── scenes
│         │       └── scene1.md
│         └── scratchpad.md
└── novel.json
novel.json must contain at a minimum these properties:
{
    code: COT
    title: Crown of Thorns
    series_title: A Chronicle of Thorns (optional in the API)
    goal: 100000
}

Others can be added as desired, but will be ignored by the API

2. Create a new project in the API

plot a book by listing scenes with word counts and percentages
(Eventually this should be an endpoint in the API)
print out scene data for a given book